    <question number="197">
        <prompt>What was the main purpose of the International Workers of the World?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To organize all workers into one revolutionary union</option>
            <option letter="b">To support craft unionism</option>
            <option letter="c">To promote capitalism</option>
            <option letter="d">To limit worker rights</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The IWW aimed to organize all workers into "One Big Union" to overthrow capitalism through industrial unionism and direct action.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question number="198">
        <prompt>What was the significance of Jacob Riis's photography?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It exposed urban poverty through visual documentation</option>
            <option letter="b">It celebrated city life</option>
            <option letter="c">It promoted tourism</option>
            <option letter="d">It supported business</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Riis's photographs exposed urban poverty conditions to middle-class audiences, helping spark progressive reform efforts in cities.</explanation>
